Right-wing or Right Wing;
Noun

Political: to be conservative in nature, to be of a political orientation that favours or values maintaining the status quo more than change or innovation.  Refers to political parties, organisations and subgroups of all groups in general.

Position oriented: to be on the right hand side of the centre, references are seen in sport, housing and military contexts.  In medieval military terms, to be on the right wing was a place of prestige, being to the right hand, the favoured hand, of the King.

